href="G1966.xml"
addr="G1966"
title="Un théorème sur les homomorphismes de schémas abéliens">G1966</fr:link>]).
        Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> be a reduced connected scheme of finite type over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex>, and let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f_1\colon  X_1\to  S]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f_2\colon  X_2\to  S]]></fr:tex> be abelian schemes over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>.
        If a morphism <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[u\colon \mathrm {R}^1{f_2}_*\mathbb {Z}\to \mathrm {R}^1{f_1}_*\mathbb {Z}]]></fr:tex> comes from a morphism <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\widetilde {u}_s\colon (X_1)_s\to (X_2)_s]]></fr:tex> of abelian varieties at some point <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s\in  S]]></fr:tex>, then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[u]]></fr:tex> comes from a (unique) morphism of abelian schemes <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\widetilde {u}\colon  X_1\to  X_2]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>

    <fr:tree
