display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  X\to  S]]></fr:tex> be a proper smooth morphism, with <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> reduced, connected, and separated.
    Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(\mathrm {R}^n f_*\mathbb {Q})^0]]></fr:tex> be the largest constant local system on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {R}^n f_*\mathbb {Q}]]></fr:tex>, with fibre <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {H}^0(S,\mathrm {R}^n f_*\mathbb {Q})]]></fr:tex>.
    Then, for each <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s\in  S]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(\mathrm {R}^n f_*\mathbb {Q})_s^0]]></fr:tex> is a Hodge sub-structure of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(\mathrm {R}^n f_*\mathbb {Q})\simeq \operatorname {H}^n(X_s,\mathbb {Q})]]></fr:tex>, and the induced Hodge structure on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {H}^0(S,\mathrm {R}^n f_*\mathbb {Q})]]></fr:tex> is independent of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
  
    
    <fr:tree
