xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>1681</fr:anchor><fr:addr
type="machine">#260</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-260.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:parent>hodge-theory-ii-4.1.2</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s\in  S]]></fr:tex>, and let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X_s=f^{-1}(s)]]></fr:tex>.
      If <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> is smooth, and if <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\bar {X}]]></fr:tex> is a smooth compactification of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>, then, by <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-ii-4.1.1"
href="hodge-theory-ii-4.1.1.xml"
taxon="Theorem"
number="4.1.1" />, the subspace <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(\mathrm {R}^n f_*\mathbb {Q})_s^0]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(\mathrm {R}^n f_*\mathbb {Q})_s]]></fr:tex> is the image of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {H}^n(\bar {X},\mathbb {Q})]]></fr:tex>.
      Since the restriction map
      <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[         \operatorname {H}^n(\bar {X},\mathbb {Q}) \to  \operatorname {H}^n(X_s,\mathbb {Q})       ]]></fr:tex>
      is a morphism of Hodge structures, its image is a Hodge sub-structure, and the induced Hodge structure on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {H}^0(S,\mathrm {R}^n f_*\mathbb {Q})]]></fr:tex>, given by the quotient of that on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {H}^n(\bar {X},\mathbb {Q})]]></fr:tex>, is independent of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
